-- Australia, New Zealand Stocks: BHP, Paperlinx Ltd., Transfield, Woodside
-- B y   S h a n i   R a j a
-- 2010-10-01T06:45:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/australia-new-zealand-stocks-bhp-paperlinx-ltd-transfield-woodside.html
Australia’s  S&P/ASX 200 Index  slipped
0.1 percent to 4,579.20 at the 4:10 p.m. close of trading in
Sydney. New Zealand’s  NZX 50 Index  gained 1.1 percent to
3,212.94 at the 5 p.m. close in Wellington.  The following were among the most active shares in the
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  Commodity stocks: Mining and oil shares rose after U.S.
reports on economic growth, unemployment and business activity
boosted confidence in a global recovery.  BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BHP AU), the world’s largest mining
company, gained 1.4 percent to A$39.46.  Rio Tinto Group  (RIO AU),
the third biggest, rose 0.4 percent to A$77.07.  Woodside
Petroleum Ltd.  (WPL AU), Australia’s second-biggest oil and gas
producer, climbed 1 percent to A$44.30.  New Zealand Oil & Gas
Ltd.  (NZO NZ) advanced 2.4 percent to NZ$1.30 in Wellington.       Monadelphous Group Ltd.  (MND AU) retreated 0.8 percent to
A$15.94. The mining services company had its rating cut to
“underperform” from “neutral” by analysts at Merrill Lynch.       Paladin Energy Ltd.  (PDN AU) gained 4.7 percent to A$3.76.
The Australian mining company producing uranium in Africa
reported a higher ore-reserve estimate for the Langer Heinrich
mine in Namibia.       Paperlinx Ltd.  (PPX AU) rose 2.3 percent to 45 Australian
cents after Australia’s largest papermaker named  Toby Marchant 
as chief executive officer from Nov. 1, replacing  Thomas Park .      Transfield Services Ltd.  (TSE AU), a provider of maintenance
services to mining and infrastructure companies, lost 1.4
percent to A$3.55 after the stock was cut to “hold” from
“buy” by analysts at Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc.  To contact the reporter for this story:
 Shani Raja  in Sydney at 
 sraja4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
